00:46:32.019 --> 00:46:35.019
How does the organization help our brothers and sisters

00:46:35.019 --> 00:46:38.019
in times of national crisis?

00:46:38.019 --> 00:46:40.019
We met two witness couples

00:46:40.019 --> 00:46:42.019
who personally experienced

00:46:42.019 --> 00:46:45.019
two of the largest terrorist attacks in recent years.

00:46:45.019 --> 00:47:05.380
Not a day goes by when we don't think about our son poorly.

00:47:05.380 --> 00:47:08.380
There was horror and suffering.

00:47:08.380 --> 00:47:11.380
Things we don't want to witness anymore.

00:47:11.380 --> 00:47:26.809
September 11th was a very scary, terrifying day.

00:47:26.809 --> 00:47:33.440
I asked for me when I really understood what was happening.

00:47:33.440 --> 00:47:34.440
I got scared.

00:47:34.440 --> 00:47:36.440
I didn't know what to do.

00:47:36.440 --> 00:47:38.440
I didn't know what to think.

00:47:39.440 --> 00:47:43.980
When the second tower fell,

00:47:43.980 --> 00:47:46.980
Paulie was on 110th floor.

00:47:46.980 --> 00:47:49.980
And everybody was shouting, crying.

00:47:49.980 --> 00:47:52.980
I was praying to Jehovah

00:47:52.980 --> 00:47:55.980
because I was heartbroken.

00:47:55.980 --> 00:48:01.630
We live on Voltaire Boulevard.

00:48:01.630 --> 00:48:03.630
It's a broad avenue.

00:48:03.630 --> 00:48:06.630
There is a concert hall called the Bataclons.

00:48:06.630 --> 00:48:09.630
When the doors of the Bataclons are open,

00:48:09.630 --> 00:48:12.630
we can hear everything that goes on inside.

00:48:15.630 --> 00:48:19.630
That night, three men entered the Bataclons concert hall

00:48:19.630 --> 00:48:22.630
and they started shooting into the crowd.

00:48:22.630 --> 00:48:25.630
We immediately grabbed our gold bags

00:48:25.630 --> 00:48:27.630
and then we sat in front of the sofa

00:48:27.630 --> 00:48:30.630
and we begged Jehovah for his holy spirit

00:48:30.630 --> 00:48:37.210
so we could face the situation.

00:48:37.210 --> 00:48:46.210
It was around 10 pm when there was a news flash

00:48:46.210 --> 00:48:49.210
that announced that there was an attack.

00:48:49.210 --> 00:48:52.210
I was in shock when I heard the news.

00:48:52.210 --> 00:48:58.210
And then I immediately thought about our brothers and sisters.

00:48:58.210 --> 00:49:01.210
I quickly got in contact with the circuit officer

00:49:01.210 --> 00:49:05.210
in order to get some news about our brothers and sisters

00:49:05.210 --> 00:49:08.210
to know how they were doing.

00:49:08.210 --> 00:49:11.210
Then, very early the next morning,

00:49:11.210 --> 00:49:13.210
we set up an emergency committee

00:49:13.210 --> 00:49:16.210
made up of several brothers from the service department.

00:49:16.210 --> 00:49:18.210
We decided to write a letter

00:49:18.210 --> 00:49:20.210
and make other arrangements

00:49:20.210 --> 00:49:23.210
to assist the friends who, in one way or another,

00:49:23.210 --> 00:49:25.210
were affected by this event.

00:49:25.210 --> 00:49:30.579
In turn, the circuit officer would make an effort

00:49:30.579 --> 00:49:33.579
to rapidly get in touch with the elders

00:49:33.579 --> 00:49:36.579
to oversee the affected territory.

00:49:39.579 --> 00:49:42.579
One of our challenges on a personal level

00:49:42.579 --> 00:49:44.579
was whether we would even be able

00:49:44.579 --> 00:49:46.579
to encourage our brothers and sisters

00:49:46.579 --> 00:49:50.579
because we had never experienced such a terrible event.

00:49:50.579 --> 00:49:53.579
We organized ourselves, we paired up as elders

00:49:53.579 --> 00:49:56.579
and headed off to do shepherding.

00:49:56.579 --> 00:50:00.579
We started calling mid-morning on Tuesday.

00:50:00.579 --> 00:50:03.579
We received a report back from all the traveling overseers

00:50:03.579 --> 00:50:05.579
by the end of Thursday.

00:50:05.579 --> 00:50:07.579
And unfortunately,

00:50:07.579 --> 00:50:10.579
we learned that 14 of our brothers and sisters

00:50:10.579 --> 00:50:13.989
had lost their lives.

00:50:13.989 --> 00:50:18.989
We knew that we needed to encourage the families.

00:50:18.989 --> 00:50:22.989
We knew that we needed to shepherd them as soon as possible.

00:50:22.989 --> 00:50:26.989
The elders immediately came.

00:50:26.989 --> 00:50:29.989
We went over the book of Job.

00:50:29.989 --> 00:50:32.989
And I just listened, you know, I was just listening.

00:50:32.989 --> 00:50:35.989
I've heard the same words before, but it was different now.

00:50:35.989 --> 00:50:37.989
The things that were being said

00:50:37.989 --> 00:50:40.989
went straight to my heart.

00:50:40.989 --> 00:50:45.989
A few days later, we were visited by two brothers from Bethel.

00:50:45.989 --> 00:50:48.989
It was very touching that they came to see us

00:50:48.989 --> 00:50:50.989
and that they were concerned about us.

00:50:50.989 --> 00:50:56.989
It shows us that Jehovah was aware of how we felt that night.

00:50:56.989 --> 00:51:00.989
Our brothers were there. They were ready to help one another out.

00:51:00.989 --> 00:51:04.989
Then there was so much empathy and love shown.

00:51:04.989 --> 00:51:08.989
When we were ultimately granted access to ground zero

00:51:08.989 --> 00:51:12.989
and we started encountering the first responders,

00:51:12.989 --> 00:51:16.989
that we let them know how much we appreciated their hard work

00:51:16.989 --> 00:51:19.989
and that they had a skill set that we didn't have.

00:51:19.989 --> 00:51:24.989
But yet our skill set was trying to offer comfort to them.

00:51:24.989 --> 00:51:26.989
We shared a scripture with them.

00:51:26.989 --> 00:51:31.989
Immediately we could tell that that was something that caused emotion

00:51:31.989 --> 00:51:33.989
to rise up in them right away.

00:51:33.989 --> 00:51:36.989
And they expressed great appreciation for that.

00:51:36.989 --> 00:51:39.989
It's one of the beautiful things about the scriptures

00:51:39.989 --> 00:51:43.989
is that they're calming, soothing, comforting.

00:51:43.989 --> 00:51:47.989
And the scriptures did not let down the workers

00:51:47.989 --> 00:51:52.300
that were there at ground zero either.

00:51:52.300 --> 00:51:56.300
The visit of the brothers from Bethel was really a gift from Jehovah.

00:51:56.300 --> 00:51:59.300
It showed his genuine interest in us.

00:51:59.300 --> 00:52:01.300
It was really wonderful.

00:52:01.300 --> 00:52:05.300
After the brothers visited us,

00:52:05.300 --> 00:52:08.300
we felt so comforted.

00:52:08.300 --> 00:52:11.300
So encouraged that we said to each other,

00:52:11.300 --> 00:52:13.300
we have to get back in the ministry

00:52:13.300 --> 00:52:16.300
and comfort people in the territory.

00:52:16.300 --> 00:52:19.300
We have to console our brothers and sisters as well.

00:52:19.300 --> 00:52:23.300
We can only thank and glorify Jehovah

00:52:23.300 --> 00:52:25.300
who really is a God of love.

00:52:25.300 --> 00:52:36.179
I kind of felt Jehovah's hands just reaching out to me,

00:52:36.179 --> 00:52:39.659
which I needed.

00:52:39.659 --> 00:52:42.659
But I cannot wait to the day that I'm totally refreshed

00:52:42.659 --> 00:52:44.659
where I can see.

00:52:44.659 --> 00:52:48.059
I can actually see Paulie.

00:52:48.059 --> 00:52:53.059
I can see him just coming back into our lives

00:52:53.059 --> 00:52:56.059
and I want to embrace him so much.

00:52:56.059 --> 00:53:02.039
After something like this, we are not the same.

00:53:02.039 --> 00:53:10.389
With the help of the organization, the brothers,

00:53:10.389 --> 00:53:13.389
Jehovah's death for us,

00:53:13.389 --> 00:53:16.389
so that is refreshing.

00:53:16.389 --> 00:53:23.760
And I thank Jehovah for what he wants to do for me,

00:53:23.760 --> 00:53:35.849
